Currently if you use the "filter =" JQL expression it takes the results from the base query, but uses the default column ordering. It would be great if, when there is no column order specifically for the new search, the column order is inherited from the base filter. This will allow really generic filters to be created with an optimal column ordering, and effectively get around the current limitation that you can't reuse column ordering.

If I use wiki markup to link to an attachment and the name of the attachment starts with a string that happens to correspond to a valid issue ID, then the attachment link is not rendered correctly.  Example:

{noformat}
!JRA-9_picture.jpg!
{noformat}

...renders as:

!JRA-9_picture.jpg!

