I created a two-dimensional filter gadget on my dashboard. I wanted the two-dimensional gadget of Status and Priority. I have a filter that has two projects. One of the projects has status types: Open, Resolved. The other project has status types: DEV: Open, DEV: Resolved. When created the two-dimensional filter gadget, it categorized the status Open as DEV: Open and Resolved as DEV: Resolved. Thus, the first project's status did not show up on the dimension.

Seems like if the status is like another type of status, it combines them to one. This is not the desirable outcome.

